name: virus black death
description: The Black Death, or the Black Death, was a severe pandemic that first hit Europe in the mid to late 14th century (1347 – 1351) and killed one-third to two-thirds of Europe's population.  The same disease is thought to have hit again. Several outbreaks of this disease were eradicated in Europe in the early 19th century, but it continues in other parts of the world (Central and Oriental Africa, Madagascar, Asia, parts of South America).
